Package manager: Bun

This project uses Bun as the package manager. Prefer Bun for installs, scripts, and tooling unless a tool explicitly requires something else.

Do

Install dependencies: bun install (not npm install, pnpm install, or yarn)
Add packages: bun add <pkg> / bun add -d <pkg>
Run scripts from package.json: bun run <script> or bun <script> when equivalent
Execute binaries: bunx <command> instead of npx when running one-off CLIs
In documentation and AI suggestions, show Bun commands by default

Avoid

Suggesting or running npm, pnpm, or yarn for this repo unless there is a documented exception

Examples

# ✅

bun install
bun run build
bun run dev
bun add zod
bunx tsc --noEmit

# ❌ (for this project)

pnpm install
npm run build

When the workspace has multiple packages (e.g. web/), run commands from the relevant package directory or use Bun’s workspace behavior as configured in the repo.
